---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" active="home">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Extended English</p>
      <h1>Macbeth, studied properly.</h1>
      <p class="lede" style="max-width:37em;">Act-by-act guides to the play, character studies that ask what each figure does to the tragedy, a bank of verified quotations, context that earns its place, and clear guidance on the Literary Heritage coursework essay. Everything here is built to feed one thing: an argued essay in your own voice.</p>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.6rem;">
        <a class="pill" href="/guide/" style="font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem; text-decoration: none;">Start with the guide &rarr;</a>
        <a class="pill" href="/coursework/" style="font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem; text-decoration: none;">The coursework, explained &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">What this site holds</h2>
      <div class="grid cols-3">
        <div class="card">
          <h3><a href="/guide/">The guide</a></h3>
          <p>All five acts, scene by scene: what happens, the methods that matter, and the quotations worth knowing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3><a href="/characters/">Characters</a></h3>
          <p>The Macbeths, Banquo, Duncan, Macduff and the Witches, read for dramatic function, not personality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3><a href="/themes/">Themes</a></h3>
          <p>Kingship, ambition, gender, the supernatural, guilt: each turned from a topic into an argument.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3><a href="/context/">Context</a></h3>
          <p>Jacobean anxieties, James I and the Gunpowder Plot, woven into analysis rather than bolted on. A third of your mark.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3><a href="/quotations/">Quotations</a></h3>
          <p>A bank organised by focus, every line checked, every one chosen because it gives you something to say.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3><a href="/coursework/">Coursework</a></h3>
          <p>The three set questions, the assessment objectives, planning, structure and the integrity rules, explained plainly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="small">Part of the Extended English family, alongside the Klara and the Sun, Kindertransport and Poetry Anthology guides.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
